# D3.2 — Future Ingestion Formats (Function-Level Breakdown)

## Purpose
Function-level breakdown for implementing D3.2 future ingestion formats (CSV/Excel, PPT, transcripts).

## Implementation Sequence
1. **Phase 1: CSV/Excel support** (highest priority - structured data)
2. **Phase 2: PPT/slides support** (educational content)
3. **Phase 3: Transcript/audio/video support** (rich media)

---

## Phase 1: CSV/Excel Support

### D3.2.1.1 — Add CSV parsing dependency
**Business Logic:** Add `papaparse` library for CSV parsing
**Scope:** `backend/package.json`
**Expected Result:** Dependencies updated
**Tests:** Verify `npm install` succeeds

---

### D3.2.1.2 — Add Excel parsing dependency
**Business Logic:** Add `exceljs` library for Excel .xlsx/.xls parsing
**Scope:** `backend/package.json`
**Expected Result:** Dependencies updated
**Tests:** Verify `npm install` succeeds

---

### D3.2.1.3 — Create CSV parser service
**Business Logic:** Parse CSV files and extract text with metadata
**Scope:** `backend/src/ingestion/csv.js`
**Expected Result:** Service with `parse(filePath)` function returning `{ text, metadata }`
**Tests:** Unit tests for basic CSV, multi-line cells, quoted values

---

### D3.2.1.4 — Create Excel parser service
**Business Logic:** Parse Excel files, extract all sheets with metadata
**Scope:** `backend/src/ingestion/excel.js`
**Expected Result:** Service with `parse(filePath)` function returning `{ text, metadata }`
**Tests:** Unit tests for single sheet, multi-sheet workbooks, formula vs value

---

### D3.2.1.5 — Update ingestion service to handle CSV/Excel
**Business Logic:** Extend `backend/src/ingestion/service.js` to route CSV/Excel files
**Scope:** `backend/src/ingestion/service.js`
**Expected Result:** MIME type detection and routing to appropriate parser
**Tests:** Integration tests with sample CSV/Excel files

---

### D3.2.1.6 — Add controller tests for CSV/Excel upload
**Business Logic:** Verify upload endpoints handle CSV/Excel files
**Scope:** `backend/src/ingestion/controller.test.js`
**Expected Result:** Test coverage for CSV/Excel upload paths
**Tests:** Jest tests for successful upload, error handling

---

### D3.2.1.7 — Update schema for CSV/Excel metadata
**Business Logic:** Extend `source_materials` table to store format-specific metadata
**Scope:** `backend/db/schema/002_csv_excel_metadata.sql`
**Expected Result:** Migration adding `content_metadata` JSONB column
**Tests:** Migration verification, schema validation

---

## Phase 2: PPT/Slides Support

### D3.2.2.1 — Add PPT parsing dependency
**Business Logic:** Add `pptx` library for PowerPoint parsing
**Scope:** `backend/package.json`
**Expected Result:** Dependencies updated
**Tests:** Verify `npm install` succeeds

---

### D3.2.2.2 — Create PPT parser service
**Business Logic:** Parse PPTX files, extract text and images from slides
**Scope:** `backend/src/ingestion/pptx.js`
**Expected Result:** Service with `parse(filePath)` function returning `{ text, images, metadata }`
**Tests:** Unit tests for slide extraction, text formatting

---

### D3.2.2.3 — Update ingestion service to handle PPTX
**Business Logic:** Extend `backend/src/ingestion/service.js` to route PPTX files
**Scope:** `backend/src/ingestion/service.js`
**Expected Result:** MIME type detection and routing to PPTX parser
**Tests:** Integration tests with sample PPTX files

---

### D3.2.2.4 — Add controller tests for PPTX upload
**Business Logic:** Verify upload endpoints handle PPTX files
**Scope:** `backend/src/ingestion/controller.test.js`
**Expected Result:** Test coverage for PPTX upload paths
**Tests:** Jest tests for successful upload, error handling

---

## Phase 3: Transcript/Audio/Video Support

### D3.2.3.1 — Create transcript parser service
**Business Logic:** Parse subtitle files (.srt, .vtt) and plain text transcripts
**Scope:** `backend/src/ingestion/transcript.js`
**Expected Result:** Service with `parse(filePath)` function returning `{ text, timestamps, metadata }`
**Tests:** Unit tests for .srt, .vtt, .txt formats

---

### D3.2.3.2 — Integrate OpenAI Whisper CLI for audio transcription
**Business Logic:** Call `openai-whisper` CLI to transcribe audio files
**Scope:** `backend/src/ingestion/whisper.js`
**Expected Result:** Service with `transcribe(filePath)` function returning `{ text, metadata }`
**Tests:** Integration tests with sample audio files (mock if Whisper unavailable)

---

### D3.2.3.3 — Update ingestion service to handle transcripts/audio
**Business Logic:** Extend `backend/src/ingestion/service.js` to route transcript/audio files
**Scope:** `backend/src/ingestion/service.js`
**Expected Result:** MIME type detection and routing to appropriate handler
**Tests:** Integration tests with sample transcript/audio files

---

### D3.2.3.4 — Add controller tests for transcript/audio upload
**Business Logic:** Verify upload endpoints handle transcript/audio files
**Scope:** `backend/src/ingestion/controller.test.js`
**Expected Result:** Test coverage for transcript/audio upload paths
**Tests:** Jest tests for successful upload, error handling

---

## Phase 4: Unified Pipeline & Documentation

### D3.2.4.1 — Update MIME type detection
**Business Logic:** Add new MIME types to ingestion router
**Scope:** `backend/src/ingestion/router.js`
**Expected Result:** MIME type mappings for CSV, Excel, PPTX, audio, video, subtitles
**Tests:** Route registration verification

---

### D3.2.4.2 — Create comprehensive integration tests
**Business Logic:** End-to-end tests for all new format uploads
**Scope:** `backend/src/ingestion/flow.integration.test.js`
**Expected Result:** Test suite covering all new formats
**Tests:** Integration tests with real sample files

---

### D3.2.4.3 — Update documentation
**Business Logic:** Document new format support in user-facing docs
**Scope:** `docs/FILE_INGESTION_STRATEGY.md`, `docs/D3.2_FUTURE_INGESTION_FORMATS_DESIGN.md`
**Expected Result:** Updated docs with implementation status
**Tests:** N/A (documentation only)

---

### D3.2.4.4 — Final commit and push
**Business Logic:** Commit all changes and push to GitHub
**Scope:** All files
**Expected Result:** All code pushed to `origin/main`
**Tests:** Git push verification

---

## Worker Assignment Protocol

1. **Assign one slice per worker** (fresh worker per slice)
2. **Timeout:** 5-10 minutes per coding slice
3. **Verify:** Check code/tests/commits after each completion
4. **Push:** Main session handles git push after verification
5. **Continue:** Immediately proceed to next slice unless blocked

## Current Status
- **D3.2 Design:** ✅ Complete (`docs/D3.2_FUTURE_INGESTION_FORMATS_DESIGN.md`)
- **Next:** Start Phase 1 (CSV/Excel) with D3.2.1.1
